By: Peter Sterry
---
The prime operation of every Intellectual Spirit is contemplation. The
first and immediate Object of its contemplation is its own Essence. In
this Glass of living and immortal Light, all other things, according
to their proper essences in their several and essential forms, appear
to it most clearly and delightfully, as its own Births and Beauties.
